def: To shut up or inclose, as in a pen. Feltham.
A division of nudibranchiate Mollusca, in which the gills forma wreath or cluster upon the posterior part of the back. SeeNudibranchiata, and Doris.
Of or relating to Alphonso X., the Wise, King of Castile (1252-1284). Alphonsine tables, astronomical tables prepared under thepatronage of Alphonso the Wise. Whewell.
A show or exhibition having a great number of scenes or views.
Of or pertaining to the pubes; in the region of the pubes; as,the pubic bone; the pubic region, or the lower part of thehypogastric region. See Pubes.(b) Of or pertaining to the pubis.

Any one of numerous species of long-winged oceanic birds of thegenus Puffinus and related genera. They are allied to the petrels,but are larger. The Manx shearwater (P. Anglorum), the duskyshearwater (P. obscurus), and the greater shearwater (P. major), arewell-known species of the North Atlantic. See Hagdon.
First in time or place; most advanced; chief in rank ordignity; as, the foremost troops of an army.THat struck the foremost man of all this world. Shak.
A machine for applying size to warp yarns.
